quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  4,80,"Whoever obeys the Messenger obeys Allah and whoever turns away, then, We did not send you to stand guard over them."
  4,81,"And they say, "Obedience (we observe)." But when they go away from you, a group of them conspires at night contrary to what they say. And Allah records what they conspire. So ignore them and put your trust in Allah. And Allah is enough to trust in."
  4,82,"Do they not, then, ponder in the Qur'an? Had it been from someone other than Allah, they would have found in it a great deal of contradiction."
  4,83,"And when there comes to them a matter about peace or fear, they spread it. Had they referred it to the Messenger and to those in authority among them, those of them who were to investigate it would have certainly known it (the' truth of the matter). But for Allah's grace upon you, and mercy, you would have followed the Satan, save a few."
  4,84,"So, fight in the way of Allah. You are not responsible but for yourself. And persuade the believers. It is likely that Allah will prevent the mischief of those who disbelieve. And Allah is the strongest in war and the mightiest in punishing."
  4,85,"And whoever makes a good recommendation, there shall be for him a share from it (in the Hereafter). And whoever makes a bad recommendation, there shall be for him a share from it. And Allah is powerful over everything."
  4,86,"And when you are greeted with a salutation, greet with one better than it, or return the same. Surely, Allah is the reckoner over everything."